title: For Sale:  Giles Colt 1911 Custom C1959 Government Model
postcontent: Hi, A Giles Custom Colt bullseye pistol 1911 Government Model 45 ACP, John Giles was a genius gunsmith who worked on 1911s and 22s during the 60s thru the 80s. He had the .45 shop in Odessa Florida and many of his 1911s shot at camp Perry along with those of James Clark. He was known for his "wagon wheel" looking sight which usually was a full rib for target and no rib for his street guns. His trademark were the welds he added to the inside of the slide to increase the lockup. Usually there was one but sometimes two or rarely three. His groups at 50 yards were phenomenal, something like 3/4 of an inch at 50 yards. This 1959 Colt is in excellent condition with 90% polished blued finish intact. Checkered Walnut Grips and the famous wagon wheel sights. This Colt will make you look good at the range with awesome groups.MN Buyer needs MN state ID and Permit.Out of MN buyer pays $30 shipping to local FFL.
